   suerinensis Friese, 1884 and A. (Poliandrena) tarsata Nylander, 1848.
   This is the second contribution concerning the rare species of the genus
   Andrena Fabricius, 1775 in Poland. The studies were based on museum
   collections as well as the author's own collections. During the
   research, approximately 21,000 specimens of mining bees of the genus
   Andrena from Poland were identified representing ninety-five taxa. The
   species discussed in the paper are known from just a few records in the
   country. The following information is provided for each species: short
