   spur morphology had similar spur anatomy and nectary trichome structure.
   In Utricularia flowers, nectar is produced by spur capitate trichomes
   (sessile or stalked). Our results showed that regardless of the various
   spur morphology, trichomes have similar architecture and ultrastructure.
   Head cells of these trichomes are transfer cells with an eccrine nectar
